The same cannot be said of Mr Saatchi, who looked dishevelled after dining at Scott’s in Mayfair on Friday – the very restaurant where the ‘throttling’ scene took place only weeks before.

He appeared exhausted as he sucked on a cigarette in the street, and later as he sat in the back of a taxi his head was bowed.

In June Miss Lawson left the marital home following the very public assault, for which Mr Saatchi has accepted a police caution, and they have barely spoken to one another since. The couple were granted a decree nisi last month.

Earlier this week Nigella finally broken her silence two months after the distressing pictures emerged.

On Tuesday night, she returned to Twitter for the first time to share a photograph of a cake she'd made to mark the return of The Great British Bake Off.

